

JDK(JAVA DEVELOPMENT KIT) - A software toolkit used to build and compile java
programs(Converts to byte code).It includes JRE and development tools.

JRE(JAVA RUNTIME ENVIRONMENT) - It provides an environment to run java programs.
The environment includes standard Libraries and JVM.

JVM(JAVA VIRTUAL MACHINE) - Its responsible for executing the java program
(Contains inbuilt and extra classes).

(compiles the code with the help of JDK and run in JVM

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

RUN TIME ERROR:
-> Occurs during program execution(While the program is running)
Eg:Division by 0
   ArrayIndexOutOfBounds
   Exceptions
   FileNotFound 
   
COMPILE TIME ERROR:
-> During compilation(code to byte code translation)
Eg: Missing semicolon
    Syntax error
    Type mismatch
    Undeclared variable
   
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DATATYPES:
1.boolean(1byte)
2.Char(2 byte)
3.byte(8 bit)
4.Short(2 byte)
5.int(4 byte)
6.long(8 byte)
7.float(4 byte)
8.double(8 byte)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TYPE CASTING:
->Explicitly converting one datatype into another(programmer)
Eg:int a=int(5.7);
   a=5;
->If we assign a value of higher to lower data type then some data will be lost.
Long->byte,short,int
float->int,byte,short

TYPE CONVERSIONS:
->Automatically converting one data type to another(compiler)
Eg:int a=10; double b=a;
  b=10.0;
->Lower data type is converted to higher data type 
byte->short,int,long,float
short->int,long,float

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ternary Operator : condition?if true:if false.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BREAK:Jumps out of the loop
CONTINUE:Used when we want to skip a specific cases inside the loop,but keep Looping.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

OOPs

1.ENCAPSULATION
2.ABSTRACTION - Hiding the unnecessary details
3.POLYMORPHISHM
4.INHERITANCE


















